rb-netchecker
    by Jonathan Clarke
    http://www.beilabs.com

== DESCRIPTION:
  
rb-netchecker is a Ruby class written to check if there is Internet access available on the current machine

== SYNOPSIS:

require('rubygems')
require('netchecker')

begin
  check = Netchecker.new()
end

result = check.check_url("google.com", 80)
puts "Checking google.com  -  Result: #{result}"
...

== REQUIREMENTS:

  * Ruby (Developed on 1.8.7)
  * RubyGems 

== INSTALL:

  sudo gem install netchecker

